meta {
  name: GET connection-status readiness
  type: http
  seq: 21
}

get {
  url: {{base_url}}/api/v2/connection-status/{{vin}}/readiness
  body: none
  auth: bearer
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{access_token}}
}

headers {
  Accept: application/json
}

docs {
  Reports whether the car's connectivity module is currently online
  and whether the car is in motion.

  Response shape: {"unreachable": bool|null, "inMotion": bool|null,
  ...}. ``unreachable=null`` is treated as ONLINE (assumes reachable
  to avoid setting is_online to a misleading false default).
  ``inMotion=true`` flips the binary_sensor.<vin>_is_driving on.

  Implementation: gathered in SkodaClient.get_status() at
  custom_components/vag_connect/cariad/api/skoda.py:157, parsed at
  the readiness branch around line 387.

  Drives: binary_sensor.<vin>_is_online, .<vin>_is_driving, and
  feeds compute_connection_state() in cariad/_util alongside the
  carCapturedTimestamp walk.
}
